<br>
If I win a bonecaster robe I can trade it for the haste item I want and the caster invariably wins because they depend on gear less. So a dragon raid im on gets a book of frost and the cleric wins it. Im sure I can buy a book of frost with the money I get from selling the red dragonscale and so on. The chain never ends.<br>
<br>
Verant intended their to be trading in this game and some servers put this rule of NBG in and it does not work. You can say it does work and you can quote your examples but we can all quote examples of how people ahve cheated the system. It may work in guild but it does not work in the open game.<br>
<br>
In guild I'll happily defer mellee items to the main warrior because he is going to be taking all the hits. He needs the greatest AC and HP. But in turn I expect him to help out with the other stuff. I expect him to say...well ok,..heres an item thats a 2AC upgrade for me but 12AC upgrade for Kerryn..how does it serve the guild best?<br>
<br>
But I won't roll on an item thats 25 AC upgrade for me when the main tank is going to gain an amount of AC that is clearly going to make him better.<br>
<br>
Guys..I'd like to make things fair and I'd like to believe that we were all in it for the good of the server. But we're not. It's never going to be fair and NBG just opens too many of those doors to abuse. Id say that the server is split almost down the middle. Some advocate NBG whilst the others don't.<br>
<br>
